This spontaneous report was received from the mother of a 20 month old male regarding Ibuprofen 40 mg/mL 
Infant Berry Suspension. The child began receiving 2 mL as needed on 07JAN2015 for a fever. On 08JAN2015, the
mother left the bottle open when she was rinsing the dosing syringe and the child accessed the bottle and ingested 
approximately 5 mL. The mother contacted Poison Control and was reportedly advised to provide the child with 
food and water and to watch for an upset stomach. On 15JAN2015 the mother confirmed that the child was fine 
and had not experienced any adverse events. Use of the product on an as needed basis continued. The child has 
no known drug allergies. No further information is expected.